%20Be%20Taken%20As%20Resignation%26quot%3B%3A%20Elon%20Musk's%20Warning%20To%20Federal%20Staff%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EElon%20Musk%2C%20the%20billionaire%20advisor%20to%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20said%20Saturday%20that%20all%20US%20federal%20employees%20must%20justify%20their%20work%20or%20lose%20their%20jobs%2C%20hours%20after%20the%20president%20pushed%20him%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bmore%20aggressive%26quot%3B%20in%20slashing%20government%20spending.%20Musk%20--%20the%20world's%20richest%20person%20and%20Trump's%20biggest%20donor%20--%20has%20led%20the%20effort%20to%20fire%20swaths%20of%20the%20government%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20federal%20employees%20will%20shortly%20receive%20an%20email%20requesting%20to%20understand%20what%20they%20got%20done%20last%20week.%20Failure%20to%20respond%20will%20be%20taken%20as%20a%20resignation%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20email%20provided%20to%20AFP%2C%20federal%20workers%20were%20asked%20to%20submit%20%26quot%3Bapprox.%205%20bullets%20of%20what%20you%20accomplished%20last%20week.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20email%20came%20from%20the%20US%20Office%20of%20Personnel%20Management%20(OPM)%2C%20with%20the%20subject%20line%20%26quot%3BWhat%20did%20you%20do%20last%20week%3F%26quot%3B.%20The%20deadline%20to%20reply%20was%2011%3A59%20pm%20Monday%2C%20though%20the%20message%20did%20not%20say%20failure%20to%20do%20so%20would%20lead%20to%20termination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20OPM%20did%20not%20immediately%20reply%20to%20AFP's%20request%20for%20comment%20on%20Saturday%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Federation%20of%20Government%20Employees%20(AFGE)%2C%20the%20largest%20federal%20employee%20union%2C%20vowed%20to%20challenge%20any%20unlawful%20terminations%20in%20a%20statement%20from%20national%20president%20Everett%20Kelley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKelley%20slammed%20Musk%20and%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20saying%20the%20move%20showed%