he%20White%20House%20and%20received%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20enthusiastic%20endorsement%3A%20Take%20some%20of%20the%20savings%20from%20billionaire%20Elon%20Musk's%20drive%20to%20cut%20government%20spending%20and%20return%20it%20to%20taxpayers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20love%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20late%20Wednesday%20on%20Air%20Force%20One%2C%20when%20asked%20about%20the%20proposal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Musk's%20target%20of%20%242%20trillion%20in%20spending%20cuts%20is%20achieved%20by%20next%20year%2C%20supporters%20of%20the%20idea%20say%20that%20about%20one-fifth%20of%20those%20funds%20could%20be%20distributed%20to%20taxpaying%20households%20in%20checks%20of%20about%20%245%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20before%20you%20start%20planning%20for%20a%20windfall%2C%20budget%20experts%20say%20such%20huge%20savings%20-%20nearly%20one-third%20of%20the%20federal%20government's%20annual%20spending%20-%20are%20highly%20unlikely.%20And%20sending%20out%20a%20round%20of%20checks%20-%20similar%20to%20the%20stimulus%20payments%20distributed%20by%20Trump%20and%20then%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20during%20the%20pandemic%20-%20could%20fuel%20inflation%2C%20economists%20warn%2C%20though%20White%20House%20officials%20dismiss%20that%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20annual%20budget%20deficit%20at%20%241.8%20trillion%20last%20year%20and%20Trump%20proposing%20extensive%20tax%20cuts%2C%20there%20will%20also%20be%20significant%20pressure%20to%20use%20all%20the%20savings%20to%20reduce%20that%20deficit%2C%20rather%20than%20pass%20on%20part%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20to%20know%20about%20the%20proposal%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20is%20this%20coming%20from%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJames%20Fishback%2C%20founder%20of%20investment%20firm%20Azoria%20Partners%20which%20he%20launched%20at%20Trump's%20Mar-a-Lago%20estate%20in%20Florida%2C%20promoted%20the%20idea%20Tuesday%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter%2C%20prompting%20Musk%20to%20respond%20that%20he%20would%20%26quot%3Bcheck%20with%20the%20president.%26quot%3B%20Fishback%20said%20there%20have%20also%20been%20%26quot%3Bbehind%20the%20scenes%26quot%3B%20conversations%20about%20the%20issue%20with%20White%20House%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20estimated%20that%20his%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%20has%20cut%20%2455%20billion%20so%20far%20-%20a%20tiny%20fraction%20of%20the%20%246.8%20trillion%20federal%20budget.%20But%20DOGE's%20public%20statements%20so%20far%20haven't%20verified%20the%20presumed%20savings%2C%20and%20its%20claims%20that%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dead%20people%20are%20fraudulently%20receiving%20Social%20Security%20have%20been%20disproven.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFishback%20supports%20having%20the%20nonpartisan%20Congressional%20Budget%20Office%20determine%20how%20much%20DOGE%20saved.%20If%20DOGE%20cuts%20%24500%20billion%20by%20July%202026%2C%20he%20said%2C%20then%20the%20checks%20would%20be%20%241%2C250%2C%20rather%20than%20%245%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20uncovered%20enormous%20waste%2C%20fraud%20and%20abuse%2C%26quot%3B%20Fishback%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20The%20Associated%20Press.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20are%20going%20to%20make%20good%20and%20pay%20restitution%20and%20then%20rewrite%20the%20social%20contract%20between%20the%20taxpayer%20and%20the%20federal%20government.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFishback%20supports%20sending%20out%20checks%2C%20rather%20than%20using%20all%20the%20money%20to%20reduce%20the%20deficit%2C%20because%20it%20would%20encourage%20Americans%20to%20seek%20out%20wasteful%20government%20spending%20%26quot%3Bin%20their%20communities%2C%20and%20report%20it%20to%20DOGE.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20am%20I%20going%20to%20get%20my%20check%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOK%2C%20let's%20slow%20down.%20According%20to%20the%20proposal%2C%20DOGE%20must%20first%20complete%20its%20work%2C%20slated%20to%20be%20done%20by%20July%202026.%20Once%20that%20happens%2C%20one-fifth%20of%20any%20savings%20could%20be%20distributed%20later%20that%20year%20to%20the%20roughly%2079%20million%20households%20that%20pay%20income%20taxes.%20About%2040%25%20of%20Americans%20don't%20pay%20such%20taxes%2C%20so%20they%20wouldn't%20get%20a%20check.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20much%20can%20DOGE%20really%20save%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EColor%20most%20economists%20and%20budget%20experts%20skeptical%20that%20its%20focus%20on%20%26quot%3Bwaste%2C%20fraud%2C%20and%20abuse%26quot%3B%20can%20actually%20reduce%20government%20spending%20by%20much.%20Budget-cutters%20from%20both%20parties%20have%20sought%20to%20eliminate%20%26quot%3Bwaste%26quot%3B%20-%20which%20doesn't%20have%20much%20of%20a%20political%20constituency%20-%20for%20decades%2C%20with%20little%20success%20in%20reducing%20the%20deficit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20moves%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration%20so%20far%20has%20been%20to%20fire%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20government%20workers%2C%20but%20such%20changes%20aren't%20likely%20to%20produce%20big%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnly%20a%20small%20share%20of%20total%20spending%20goes%20to%20federal%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Douglas%20Elmendorf%2C%20former%20director%20of%20the%20Congressional%20Budget%20Office.%20%26quot%3BThe%20big%20money%20is%20in%20federal%20benefits%20and%20in%20federal%20taxes%20and%20those%20are%20not%20in%20DOGE's%20purview.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%2C%20John%20DiIulio%20Jr.%2C%20a%20political%20scientist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%2C%20wrote%20in%20an%20essay%20for%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%20that%20%26quot%3Beliminating%20the%20entire%20federal%20civilian%20workforce%20would%20leave%20in%20place%20about%2095%25%20of%20all%20federal%20spending%20and%20the%20%2434%20trillion%20national%20debt.''%20DiIulio%20noted%20that%20government%20contractors%20and%20nonprofits%20that%20receive%20government%20funds%20now%20employ%20three%20times%20as%20many%20people%20as%20the%20federal%20government's%202.2%20million%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20not%20clear%20how%20much%20in%20savings%20can%20be%20achieved%20without%20Congress%20codifying%20it%20in%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFiring%20someone%20doesn't%20save%20money%20until%20Congress%20comes%20back%20and%20reduces%20the%20appropriation%20for%20that%20employee's%20agency%2C%26quot%3B%20Elmendorf%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20fire%20somebody%20but%20leave%20the%20appropriation%20where%20it%20is%2C%20then%20...%20that%20money%20can%20be%20spent%20on%20something%20else.%20So%20DOGE%20can't%20really%20achieve%20savings%20until%20there's%20legislative%20change%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWouldn't%20another%20round%20of%20government%20checks%20contribute%20to%20higher%20inflation%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20and%20his%20economists%20blame%20Biden's%20%241%2C400%20stimulus%20checks%2C%20distributed%20in%20the%20spring%20of%202021%2C%20for%20fueling%20the%20worst%20spike%20in%20inflation%20in%20four%20decades.%20Yet%20they%20maintain%20that%20sending%20checks%20stemming%20from%20reduced%20government%20spending%20wouldn't%20boost%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKevin%20Hassett%2C%20director%20of%20the%20White%20House's%20National%20Economic%20Council%2C%20said%20Thursday%20that%20since%20the%20money%20would%20have%20been%20spent%20by%20the%20government%20anyway%2C%20having%20it%20spent%20by%20consumers%20would%20be%20a%20wash.%20Biden%20and%20Trump's%20stimulus%20checks%20during%20the%20pandemic%20were%20deficit-financed%2C%20which%20can%20be%20more%20inflationary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Ernie%20Tedeschi%2C%20director%20of%20economics%20at%20the%20Yale%20Budget%20Lab%2C%20and%20an%20economist%20in%20the%20Biden%20White%20House%2C%20said%20that%20more%20government%20checks%20are%20%26quot%3Bthe%20last%20thing%20we%20need%20economically%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20U.S.%20unemployment%20rate%20is%20now%20much%20lower%20than%20in%202021%2C%20Tedeschi%20said%2C%20which%20means%20that%20businesses%20could%20struggle%20to%20hire%20enough%20workers%20to%20meet%20the%20additional%20demand%20created%20by%20a%20round%20of%20checks.%20Worker%20shortages%20can%20push%20up%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20some%20Democrats%20agree%20with%20Hassett%2C%20but%20for%20different%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20imagine%20they'd%20be%20inflationary%20because%20I%20can't%20imagine%20they'd%20be%20big%20enough%2C''%20said%20Elaine%20Kamarck%2C%20senior%20fellow%20in%20governance%20studies%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKamarck%2C%20who%20worked%20with%20Vice%20President%20Al%20Gore%20to%20cut%20government%20waste%20in%20the%20Clinton%20administration%2C%20dismissed%20the%20DOGE%20dividend%20as%20%26quot%3Bridiculous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20money%20there%2C%20and%20certainly%20not%20enough%20money%20to%20make%20a%20big%20contribution%20to%20taxpayers%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20guy%20just%20says%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added%2C%20referring%20to%20Musk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740276120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fmmgmmn2g_donald-trump-elon-musk_625x300_23_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhow-donald-trump-can-return-savings-from-elon-musks-doge-to-us-taxpayers-7773392%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20idea%20first%20proposed%20on%20social%20media%20has%20bubbled%20up%20to%20the%20White%20House%20and%20received%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20enthusiastic%20endorsement%3A%20Take%20some%20of%20the%20sav