ired%20a%20walker%20or%20wheelchair%20at%20times%2C%20and%20the%20cold%20got%20to%20him%20more%20than%20ever.%20It%20became%20clear%20he%20needed%20the%20respite%20of%20a%20southern%20migration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20generation%20of%20men%20in%20Florida%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b73ae5eb4be2fff9a51927%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22540%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20went%20on%20a%20road%20trip%20with%20his%20dad%20and%2094-year-old%20grandfather.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20the%2094-year-old%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-secrets-of-longevity-from-99-year-old-wwii-veteran-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20War%20II%20vet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20his%20motorcycle%20and%20car%20enthusiast%20son%20(my%20father)%2C%20and%20a%20naive%20recent%20college%20grad%20who%20thought%20they%20knew%20more%20about%20the%20world%20than%20they%20did%20(me)%20loaded%20the%20Trailblazer%20and%20followed%20the%20birds.%20Grandpa%20sat%20in%20the%20back%20seat%20with%20his%20face%20against%20the%20window%20while%20my%20father%20and%20I%20split%20driving%20duties%20in%20the%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stretch%2095%20from%20the%20George%20Washington%20Bridge%20through%20New%20Jersey%20was%20always%20brutal%2C%20but%20hitting%20Delaware%20was%20like%20seeing%20the%20greener%20grass%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20fence.%20Now%2C%20state%20sizes%20would%20fluctuate%2C%20traffic%20would%20subside%2C%20and%20we'd%20ease%20into%20the%20relief%20of%20warmth.%20This%20is%20where%20my%20grandfather%20found%20great%20joy%20in%20tracking%20the%20milemakers%20on%20the%20side%20of%20the%20road.%20He'd%20call%20out%20each%20green%20sign%20as%20we%20progressed%2C%20%26quot%3B10%20miles%20to%20Maryland.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20we%20hit%20the%20gauntlet%20of%20the%20Chesapeake%20and%20mid-Atlantic.%20Baltimore%20tunnel%20can%20add%20hours%20to%20the%20already%20bullish%20commute%2C%20and%20DC%20is%20like%20playing%20traffic%20Russian%20roulette.%20Luckily%2C%20the%20old%20man%20knew%20the%20detours%20of%20these%20areas%2C%20and%20we%20passed%20the%20Mason-Dixon%20with%20comparative%20ease.%20The%20shift%20in%20the%20environment%20led%20to%20Grandpa%20spinning%20some%20new%20yarns%3A%20his%20zig%20zag%20train%20ride%20in%20the%20war%20that%20brought%20him%20to%20Fort%20Bragg%2C%20the%20time%20he%20nearly%20sold%20his%20Cadillac%20to%20a%20stranger%20at%20a%20gas%20station%20on%20this%20route%2C%20stealing%20oranges%20from%20a%20golf%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20external%20temperature%20had%20barely%20changed%20from%20New%20England%2C%20but%20he%20was%20getting%20warmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20after%20reading%20every%20billboard%20between%20the%20Carolinas%20aloud%2C%20he%20took%20a%20long%20nap.%20There%20was%20a%20sort%20of%20silent%20understanding%20between%20my%20father%20and%20me%2C%20knowing%20this%20trip%20might%20be%20the%20last%20of%20its%20kind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a039dc75-d923-441d-83ca-55798a48057f%5C%22%3EIt%20was%20his%20last%20trip%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20about%20an%2018-hour%20trek%2C%20we%20hit%20the%20Sunshine%20State.%20You%20could%20see%20the%20smile%20light%20up%20on%20the%20old%20man's%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20week%2C%20we%20pushed%20the%20wheelchair%20down%20the%20Hollywood%20boardwalk%2C%20stopping%20for%20an%20occasional%20cold%20beer%20at%20tiki%20bars%20or%20street%20vendors.%20My%20grandfather%20was%20in%20complete%20awe%20by%20the%20wave%20pool%20at%20Margaritaville%2C%20watching%20would-be%20surfers%20tumble%20into%20the%20chlorinated%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stories%20continued%2C%20too.%20I%20learned%20my%20grandfather%20was%20born%20on%20a%20kitchen%20table.%20Our%20ultimate%20patriarch%20(his%20father)%20had%20blue%20eyes%2C%20a%20rarity